  <source>German Cancer Research Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to tests the hypothesis, that N-acetylcysteine (a
      thiol-antioxidant)improves the exercise training effect on cancer patients that experience
      weight loss (cachexia) as assessed by muscle mass and function as well as histomorphology.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
